#Feature: System Displays Initial View

## Key
RAIL-109

## Description
As the system,
I want the UI to request the inital dataset and the backend returns an empty/default response when the Contract Profile page loads,
so that the UI can render the table structure and display all appropriate empty state.

## Acceptance Criteria

@SystemInitialPageLoadNoRows
Scenario: Initial page load returns an empty dataset
    Given the backend contains no contract profile records
    When the Contract Profile page loads
    Then the system retunrs an empty dataset
    And the response includes table metadata
    And the UI displays zero rows
    And the UI shows a "No records found" message

## Assumption
The system assumes teh user is authorized to view the page.
Authorization for now is for read only.
The UI triggers the initial dataset request.
No search filters are applied on initial load.
Backend may return zero records.
Table metadata must always be returned.

